org.batfish.specifier

Class LocationIpSpaceSpecifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.specifier.LocationIpSpaceSpecifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IpSpaceSpecifier

    public final class LocationIpSpaceSpecifier
extends Object
implements IpSpaceSpecifier
    Specify the IpSpace inferred from a set of locations (specified by a LocationSpecifier). This set of "IpSpace locations" is independent of the set of locations that are to be assigned IpSpaces, which input via the resolve(java.util.Set<org.batfish.specifier.Location>, org.batfish.specifier.SpecifierContext) method (we could call these the "assignment locations"). All the inferred IpSpaces are unioned together into a single large space, which is then assigned to each assignment location.

    Example: We want to analyze the behavior of a set of packets starting at a core router, where the packets look like they were sent from some set of hosts. Here, the IpSpace locations are the host locations, and the assignment locations are the core router locations.

        public IpSpaceAssignment resolve(Set<Location> key,
                                 SpecifierContext ctxt)
        Description copied from interface: IpSpaceSpecifier
        Resolve the specifier into concrete IpSpaces.
        Specified by:
        resolve in interface IpSpaceSpecifier
        Parameters:
        key - The @{link Location}s for which concrete IpSpaces are needed. Which concrete IpSpace is specified may (or may not) vary with Location.
        ctxt - Information about the network that may be used to resolve concrete IpSpaces.
        Returns:
        A multimap that assigns IpSpaces to sets of the input Location. It is required that the set of values of the multimap matches exactly the input Locations, and that no Location is assigned more than one IpSpace.
